In short, global variables make the program’s state unpredictable. Every function call becomes potentially dangerous, and the programmer has no easy way of knowing which ones are dangerous and which ones aren’t! Local variables are much safer because other functions can not affect them directly.There are plenty of other good reasons not to use non-const globals.With global variables, it’s not uncommon to find a piece of code that looks like this:void someFunction()
